! $Id: whowas_userhost,v 1.1 2001/12/08 21:44:11 toast Exp $
Usage: FORMAT WHOWAS_USERHOST <format description>
  Controls how the whowas line displaying a user's userhost appears.  This
  is always the first line of output for the WHOWAS command.

  Valid format characters:
       N          Nick of whowas target
       I          The whowas target's username
       H          The whowas target's hostname or IP address

  This format has no effect if OLD_WHOIS_FORMAT is ON.

See Also:
  FORMAT WHOIS_ADMIN
  FORMAT WHOIS_AWAY
  FORMAT WHOIS_CHANNELS
  FORMAT WHOIS_IDLE
  FORMAT WHOIS_IRCNAME
  FORMAT WHOIS_NSLOOKUP
  FORMAT WHOIS_OPER
  FORMAT WHOIS_SERVER
  FORMAT WHOIS_SIGNON
  FORMAT WHOIS_USERHOST
  SET OLD_WHOIS_FORMAT
  WHOWAS
